        <TD bgcolor='dimgray' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana, Arial, Helvetica' size='2'>I've said it once and I'll say it again.  Everything's relative.  Free damage? Bah.  Get a shissar deathspeaker staff.  Soul Well is a splurt type drain life that is much better IMO than our epic effect.(and arguably easier to get) And besides, what's free damage to a necro anyways? It's not like we die because we run out of mana.  We die because we are summoned or if monster resists snare and overwhelms us.  Sure, free damage on a raid is cool, but you are not operating at peak efficiency just because you use no mana to do damage.  Remember, you have to wait for OTHER casters to regen their mana too.  Just because you're fm doesn't mean your raid leader will pull, so you're either going to be pumping mana at a highly inefficient rate into another caster or you're going to be sitting on your ass with FM.  Either way, the prospect isn't looking too favorable, especially compared to other epics.</P><P>The epic is not useless as Zrazzt says, but to think that it is anywhere near the other casters' epics is absurd.  Even the druid epic.  Do druids, I ask you, get a snare dot before they get their epic? The answer is N-O.  They receive alot with the snare DoT.  By the logic of Verant giving druids a snare dot, we should be receiving druid regen spells on our epic.  Do we? No, we get a near replica of our level 49th spell, and a spell we so seldomly use on raids b/c of its relative resistance rate and the much safer route of having a druid/ran snare.  Do shamans receive a replica of their disease/poison line? Heck no.  They receive a mana-free Splurt - the ONLY magic based DoT they get.  I'd settle for an ice-based DoT on the necro epic.  I'd even settle for the wizzie's mana/regeant free shield of four.  This is not even mentioning the uber epics mages, chanters, and clerics receive.</P><P>The end point is: other classes gain tremendous power/desirability through their epics(epic cleric=probably most desired class on my server next to epic chanters), the necro gains little.  Heck, I'd even go as far as to say the necro, wizard, shaman, and druid epics are underpowered compared to the other guys'.  But the necro is the worst of the lot, hands down, and that's all that really matters.  Someone has to be on the bottom, I know, but for once I'd like it not be necros.</P><P><BR>Etadanik the Redeemed</font></td>
