        <TD bgcolor='dimgray' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana, Arial, Helvetica' size='2'>I agree completely with Maradon on this.  I personally use darkness for 2 things; either to snare or to do damage, but rarely are both a concern.</P><P>When snaring, I will ALWAYS use dooming.  If a mob resists darkness and you have a high damage output group, its very possible that during your attempts to get darkness to stick, the mob is already running.  Worse yet, every second your waiting for that spell timer to tick down is a second you cant cast any other spells.  Not a good situation to be in the middle of an 8 second cast when you desperately need to get an ST off.</P><P>If I'm soloing in Sebilis or something, I'll use devouring because of 2 reasons:</P><P>1. It does a ton of damage<BR>2. With demi lich running, the higher mana cost of dooming vs. devouring is a moot point.  I want the high damage output version of darkness I can cast.<BR>I can solo a sebilite golem and after dropping pyrocuor, devouring, cessation, vexing and splurt, I'll drop a final vexing and med back to almost 4 bubbles of mana.  In this case, the damage output is my main concern.  If I had the epic, I would probably still use devouring because it does more damage, it casts faster and the mana isn't going to make or break me.</P><P>It angers me to no end that VI bends us over twice on our epic.  Not only is it easily one of (if not) the toughest epic to get, its also the one with the most questionably useful effect:</P><P>You will never run into an enchanter bitching about mana free haste.<BR>You will never find a cleric begrudging mana free revivisence.<BR>You'll probably have a hard time finding a shaman that looks their gift spell in the mouth.<BR>I doubt many mages complain about a pet which is hands down the best (summonable) pet in the game.<BR>Rangers probably don't mutter too much about a weapon which gives them the best wearable haste they can get and another which has a significant slow effect.<BR>Rumor has it, rogues are pretty content with their nice little knife.  Hell, I know some rogues who aren't even in a guild and still managed to get their epic.<BR>etc, etc.</P><P>=-=-=-=-=-=-=<BR>Aildrik T'Quetzl<BR>L60 Warlock<BR>[Circle of Souls]<BR>Tarew Marr </P><P>"Here in this darkness<BR>I know what I've done<BR>I know all at once who I am...</font></td>
