      <TR>
        <TD bgcolor='dimgray' valign='top' nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana, Arial, Helvetica' size='2'>Zyrixx</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='dimgray' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana, Arial, Helvetica' size='2'>I do not disagree with Ven that it is free damage. That is obvious. I also do not disagree that it is probably the best prime hand(single hand) weapon in the game for Necros. These things I agree on. Where I disagree is on the fact of its usefulness. </P><P>Perhaps he has found it to be useful to him...who knows, perhaps I could find some sort of use for it...or just use it for kicks. But I think we can all agree that darkness is mainly a soloing tool spell. </P><P>The original designers of the Necro class knew this. They knew that by combining darkness and fear along with lifetaps and drains, combined with roots and pets...we were meant to be a solo class. Today I believe they have lost sight of what the Necro is. I dont think the original designers of the Necro are still involved with EQ. They have taken the vision of those designers and warped it to suit their own vision. It just doesnt work well that way. They have poked and prodded the Necro class until even they dont know exactly what the class is supposed to be. Damage? Support? Solo? Group? All of the above? None of the above? The gravity of the whole situation is this...Verant has blurred the lines of class definition and left it all up to us to figure it out. In this process a great myriad of concepts, ideas, and playstyles have evolved. Everyone feels their playstyle works and should be considered, and some defend it to the end. What we need to do is agree to disagree on certian aspects of the Necro class. It is obvious that nobody is going to convince the entire community to play their way, or think their playstyle is the only style. Because of Verants constant changing, nerfing, moving and removing of this class, we as a community are devided. Until Verant decides on just what they want the Necro class to do it will remain devided. Devided by those who are content to be backup support, and those who believe the Necro should be a damage dealing class, viable in either a group or solo situation...whichever Verant decides. </P><P>We will remain devided when it comes to the Epic as well. Just achieving the goal of this quest is a feat, due great respect for those who have the drive and motivation to finish it. But again, some will see this as less than Epic. The quest itself may be equal to that of epic preportions..but to some the reward is greatly lacking. Not only in effect, but in appearance as well. I personally do not care one way or the other if I ever get this item. I hardly ever, if at all, solo anymore. Its boring, its beyond difficult, and the reward gained from it is miniscule at best. I prefer to hang out with my friends, doing what little I can on raids. I am a grouping Necro, but I am not completely sure Necros belong in groups. I can solo if need be, but I am not convinced that Verant really wants people to solo anymore. So to me, we are a class without a purpose. Our damage on raids can be negated by a melee in about 4 seconds, and our spells which cast so slow and take so long to take full effect never see that end. We are minimal damage and minimal support. </P><P>I do believe the myth of the Necros godly power is still very much alive in EQ. But it is just that...a myth. Surrounded by rumors and hearsay about soloing planar mobs with ease, and FD camping gaining level after level while the player sleeps. These have lit the fires in Verant forge, and the Vision has shaped us into something that none of us can truely identify. Perhaps one day things will be set right. Perhaps one day the Epic will server a purpose in my eyes and the eyes of others. But until that day, I will think of it as a symbol of just how little Verant thinks about the Necro class.</P><P></P><P>Edited by - Zyrixx on 05/03/2001  23:16:53</font></td>
