        <TD bgcolor='dimgray' valign='top' nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana, Arial, Helvetica' size='2'>Zyrixx</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='dimgray' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana, Arial, Helvetica' size='2'>I'll answer your first question. No, I do not have my epic, nor am I compelled to go after it. The only thing I would seriously use it for would be the stat boosts. I dont know why I was singled out for this question seeing as there were many many others who stated that they hated this item as well. It almost feels like a hint of an attack.</P><P>I have always been a firm believer in peoples opinions. I try my best to stay calm and sometimes friendly when posting, and I will more often than not respect the opinion of someone else if it differs from mine. I personally feel Enchanters are extremely useful. Wizards are still very useful. Eventhough many of them may try to convince me otherwise, its just how I feel and shouldnt be taken too personally by anyone who plays those classes. I would hope someone would respect my opinion as well. </P><P>When I say that we are minimal damage its because from MY experience, its true. Even in a run of the mill exp group, the mobs will last maybe 10 seconds, maybe a little longer. Other than a DD spell that melees really get upset over if you use, and a small 220 or 160 DD, thats it for those. We have to rely on DoTs for damage and our faster DoTs will take at least 45 seconds to take full effect, so in essence, we are doing minimal damage. </P><P>Im glad that you are still useful on your server, or at least you have found happiness with the role you have. I wont sit here and say I never get invited on raids, because I do quite often..but its because the people I raid with are my friends, not because I am really needed there. Many a raid have I sat there doing almost nothing. Plane raids especially, I find myself only casting BoD to heal myself from Lich...so I can in turn keep Enchanters and Clerics casting. Ah ha! you a may say. Well, to some people this is a awesome ability. You can sit there and tell yourself that you are saving the day, but have you ever had a Cleric tell you not to worry about mana pumping because he had C2? Well, now what do you do? You know what I do? I go up to mobs and /dance with them, and I cast Voice Graft on my pet and say really strange things just to play the clown for my friends. I just do not see how the piddly amounts of mana that I dish out are actually doing anything to save 20 to 30 people. Nobody has ever said, "Boy its a good thing Zyrixx was here to pump mana into us or wed all be dead." Maybe they say that to you...I dont know. But Im glad you have found happiness pumping mana and summoning corpses. I still believe the Necro should be a damage dealing class, not a support class. This is of course my opinion.</P><P>Let me tell you a little something that really has nothing to do with the epic, but with just how out of balance casters are nowadays. First off, I am not simply saying Necros are the only class in the game that is getting a shaft. I happen to think all of the pure casting classes are getting a raw deal and the example I will give only goes to reinforce that belief. I was on a raid into Kael recently. In my group was a level 54 Necro, 55 Wizard, 53 Mage, 54 Druid, 50 Warrior, and Myself 53(sorta 54) Necro. We only had two groups in Kael that night and the other group had a 56 Cleric, 53 Warrior, 55 Ranger(with epics), 52 Chanter, and a 55 Druid. Now you would think that a group consisting of mainly the "big boomers" of the casting world could easily take the kills. With a Lure/IC using wiz, a lava bolt/49 Earth pet summoned with focus item Mage, a Splurt/BoD/49 tank pet casting Necro, another Asystole/Plague/Drain Soul/53 rogue pet casting Necro, a warrior using Wyrmslayer, and a Druid throwing out DoTs...youd think it would have been so one sided...but it wasnt. We got maybe 3 kills out of 3 or 4 hours in Kael. The melee group took nearly all of them. This isnt the first time Ive witnessed this sort of thing either. Ive seen it in PoH and PoF many times. Pure caster groups get blown out of the water by melees, and to me THAT is imbalanced. Im not saying melees should be nerfed or they shouldnt be doing mass damage...what I am saying is that we as casters are supposed to be the heavy artillary. Tanks are supposed to be the immovable walls between us and the mobs. Wizards got the big guns, Mages have the next size down, and us Necros are the silent killers. But this is no longer so. So in a sense my complaints are not merely for the Necro class, but all casters. I only post my feelings on Necros here because this being a Necro board, it seems appropriate. </P><P>Please do not get me wrong. I respect you for getting the epic. I envy you for having the patience and drive to get it. I also envy you because you have found the good in it, as I simply cannot. I envy you because you can simply accept the fact that you will pump mana and be there incase they need corpses summoned. I cannot be satisfied with just that, especially after playing a Necro for so long and witnessing the once wonderful power and potential of the class. Not just the spell power we wielded, but the power and lure of the role of the Necro. So again, dont get me wrong. If you enjoy your epic, and you still feel needed and powerful as a Necro, then I can respect that. Please do not damn me because I happen to feel and think differently.</P><P> </font></td>
