w class its our job.<<</P><P>I have started a couple new classes. I have a 37 Ogre Warrior, a 15 DE Rogue, and a 5 High Elf Cleric. My guild urged me to make the cleric...they think I would be good at it, since I have an urge to take more of an active roll in battles...and we need clerics. heh</P><P><BR>>>Hmmm i see why you say your useless on raids. i would be too if i was dancing with mobs and casting the voice spell =)<<</P><P>heh heh Well, I dont ALWAYS do these things. Only when I have nothing better to do. If the Cleric is high on C2 and hes not having any mana concerns, then yes...I'll goof off. I'll attempt my best at tanking the mob or whatever. Just because Im a Necro doesnt mean Im busy all the time. heh heh</P><P><BR>>>Actually clerics have thanked me. Shamans have thanked me. When it saves 5 mins of medding for them it adds up. In hard pulls or fighting uber mobs with over the 36k kunark hp limit twiching is very important.<<</P><P>Possibly. I have yet to run across alot of the really super HP mobs of Velious yet. I do know that some of the regular mobs are very resistant...so Im not looking forward to coming across one of these bigger mobs. Im not saying I dont get thanked...by my friends of course...but then again I thank them if they cast a buff on me...I think its more just common courtesy than anything else. Have you ever been dubbed as the hero of the raid because you were mana pumping? Or did the Chanter and Cleric get all the praise for keeping mobs mezzed and tanks healed? I dunno..it just seems like as a secondary support class, we are unsung and unrecognized heros. Not that I seek acclaim or fanfair, but it would be nice to know that all of the mana that I just cant use that is going to the local Cleric is actually helping the raid along...instead of just being some sort of nameless machine.</P><P><BR>>>May not be fair our job is that but it is. Picture a cleric saying i don't like healing. A shaman refusing to buff. A mage saying i hate pets! That is what its like for a necro to say i don't like twiching and scing. Get used to it or start a new class.<<</P><P>I dont agree. If a Cleric said "I dont like healing." a Shaman said "I dont like buffing." or a Mage said "I dont like pets." would be truely silly, because thats what they do from day one(well mages get pets at level 4..but you get the gist). They start off doing those things, its what they do all their lives and they know this going in or shortly thereafter. Necros however did not always have mana pumps and corpse summons. These spells were introduced out of guilt by Verant. They went back on their own PR and nerfed a "necro ability" for the sake of Mages(another thing they said theyd never do...nerf one class to make another better). Nothing has changed with the mana pumps spells to make them better. They have remained the same since Verant put them in. Only the players have made it so that this "original ability" is the only needed ability of the necro class in groups. We also recieved Asystole and our Scent line as well with these spells. You would have thought that if we were to be a true support class, then they would have provided means to at least be good at it. I really cannot think of another support class that isnt really that great at support. Chanters and Shaman buff, Clerics heal and buff, Druids buff, Bards can improve movement and provide buffs all the while doing damage, and these classes do these things rather well too. My argument is if we are supposed to be something, at least we should be good at it. As it stands now, we do many things, but we do not excell in any one thing.</P><P><BR>>>With melee better damage delay weapons means more damage. Casters really have no way of increasing there damage short of right click items. Its the flaw in the game. Melee will greatly outdamage casters.<<</P><P>I agree...it is a flaw in the game. Magic should always be more powerful than mortal man and simple muscle. Otherwise its no longer magical, but instead boring special effects.</P><P><BR>>>Honestly get used to it now. At level 60 a rogue with a rb is a very scary weapon. Melee out damages my wizard chain nuking easy. Casters at 60 theres no way to get better melee they get better damage delay weapons and there damage out put gets alot bigger.<<</P><P>Oh, Im used to it. Its gotten to the point where its comical really. All of us casters, at the risk of our own lives, will all plan for a full mana burn to try to take the kill. I never said I liked it though...but I am used to it. ;) </P><P><BR> </font></td>
